-- Golden Eagle Retail Said to Allocate $344.8 Million Loan
-- B y   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-02-08T11:41:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/golden-eagle-retail-said-to-allocate-344-8-million-loan-1-.html
Golden Eagle Retail Group Ltd. 
allocated the equivalent of $344.8 million in a three-year loan
among 17 lenders, according to a person with direct knowledge of
the matter.  Bookrunners Hang Seng Bank Ltd. and HSBC Holdings Plc
committed $50 million each to the facility, said the person, who
declined to be identified because the details are private.
Standard Chartered Plc, Citigroup Inc. and Fubon Financial
Holding Co., who are also bookrunners on the deal, committed
HK$351 million ($45 million), $40 million and $35 million
respectively, the person said.  Bank of East Asia Ltd. committed HK$156 million, Yuanta
Commercial Bank Co. is lending HK$80 million, while Cathay
United Bank Co. pledged HK$78 million and Hua Nan Commercial
Bank Ltd. committed $4.5 million, according to the person.  Bank of  Taiwan , Bank Sinopac, Chinatrust Commercial Bank,
E.Sun Commercial Bank Ltd., First Commercial Bank Co.,
Industrial Bank of Taiwan, Mega International Commercial Bank
Co., and Taiwan Cooperative Bank Ltd. committed $10 million
each, the person said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
